From 9c42c4d4e22dc5ac3bd9455abb01794d3dfdd79c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Abdullah Nasir <abdullah@iseewaves.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 06:57:03 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix WHOIS org-data honesty, social-presence false positives,
 and add real DNSBL threat feed to URL Risk

1. WHOIS parser: add missing field-alias variants (British 'Organisation'
   spelling, registrant/admin/tech org variants). Also detect registries
   that deliberately withhold registrant data at the protocol level
   (e.g. PKNIC/.pk publishes only nameservers+dates+status by policy) and
   show an honest notice instead of a bare '-' that looked like a bug.

2. Company Footprint social presence checker: fixed a real logic bug
   where bot-protected platforms (LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram,
   Crunchbase) were marked 'Confirmed' whenever they returned HTTP 200 -
   but these platforms serve a 200 login-wall/soft-404 page for almost
   any slug regardless of whether the page exists. Now only genuinely
   verifiable platforms (GitHub, X) can be marked found; the rest always
   surface as 'Unverifiable (bot-protected)'.

3. URL Risk module: the blacklist was explicitly a small hardcoded demo
   list ('not a live threat feed' per its own docstring). Added a real
   DNSBL client (dnsbl_client.py) querying Spamhaus DBL and SURBL - the
   same free, no-signup, no-API-key technique production mail servers
   use. A live listing now forces the risk level to dangerous regardless
   of other signals, and the report shows which list(s) and category
   matched.
